# ============================================================
# STATUS DETAIL OPERATIONS
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: operations
domain: detail
subdomain: status-detail
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

purpose:
Defines operational handling for status detail.

scope:
Covers severity and reason review,
escalation response, recovery-history inspection,
and containment of unsafe status exposure.

required_behavior:
- Support severity and reason review.
- Support escalation-response operations.
- Support recovery-history inspection.
- Support containment of unsafe cause disclosure.
- Support correction and revalidation workflow.

state_model:
status_detail_operational_state:
- prepared
- reviewed
- active
- degraded
- escalated
- recovered
- archived
- contained

validation_rules:
- target_ref and status_code are required.
- severity must be valid.
- blocked or terminal detail must include a reason.
- restricted root-cause detail must not be exposed to unauthorized consumers.

transition_rules:
- prepared -> reviewed
- reviewed -> active
- active -> degraded
- degraded -> escalated
- escalated -> recovered
- recovered -> active
- active -> archived
- active -> contained
- contained -> reviewed

operational_focus:
- incident triage
- status correction review
- degraded-to-recovered tracking
- cause-disclosure containment

failure_codes:
- STATUS_DETAIL_OP_REF_MISSING
- STATUS_DETAIL_OP_CODE_MISSING
- STATUS_DETAIL_OP_SEVERITY_INVALID
- STATUS_DETAIL_OP_REASON_REQUIRED
- STATUS_DETAIL_OP_CAUSE_SCOPE_VIOLATION
